# Winnow Context Management Rules

## What is Winnow?
Winnow is a semantic context store for AI agents. It stores, searches, and versions knowledge chunks using vector embeddings.

## MCP Configuration
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "winnow": {
      "url": "https://winnow-api.xferops.dev/mcp",
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer dk_live_YOUR_KEY_HERE" }
    }
  }
}
```

## Core Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `search_context` | Semantic search — always run this first |
| `read_context` | Fetch a chunk by ID |
| `write_context` | Store a new chunk with embedding |
| `update_context` | Update a chunk (creates new version) |
| `get_context_versions` | View version history of a chunk |
| `compact_context` | Bulk-fetch chunks for summarization |
| `review_context` | Rate a chunk's quality (1-5) |
| `delete_context` | Remove a chunk |

## Coding Conventions

### API Key Format
```
dk_live_{org}_{random}   — production
dk_test_{org}_{random}   — testing
```
Never hardcode. Use `WINNOW_API_KEY` env var.

### Go API Pattern
```go
result, err := client.SearchContext(ctx, &winnow.SearchRequest{
    ProjectID: cfg.ProjectID,
    Query:     "search query",
    Limit:     10,
})
```

### REST Endpoints
```
POST   /api/context              — write_context
GET    /api/context/:id          — read_context
PUT    /api/context/:id          — update_context
DELETE /api/context/:id          — delete_context
GET    /api/context/:id/versions — get_context_versions
POST   /api/context/search       — search_context
POST   /api/context/compact      — compact_context
POST   /api/context/:id/review   — review_context
```

## Workflow Rules

### Before writing new context
1. ALWAYS `search_context` first
2. If relevant chunk exists, `update_context` instead of creating duplicate
3. One concept per chunk

### Tagging conventions
```
["research", "<topic>"]              — research findings
["plan", "<feature>", "<milestone>"] — plans
["decision", "<area>"]               — architectural decisions
["onboarding", "overview"]           — overview docs
["compacted", "<topic>"]             — merged chunks
["convention", "<area>"]             — coding standards
```

### Chunk quality
- Size: 100–600 words
- Tags: minimum 2
- Source: always include URL or file path when available

## Workflow Shortcuts

### Research a topic
```
search_context → read top results → gather new info → write_context
```

### Start a task
```
search_context(topic) → search_context(conventions) → plan → write_context(plan)
```

### End of session
```
write_context(session summary, tags=["session", date, feature])
```

## Testing
Use `dk_test_*` keys. Never use production keys in tests.
